{{punctuation marks}}
==English==

===Punctuation mark===
'''!'''

# The symbol, ''!'' (called an ''[[exclamation mark]]'' or ''[[exclamation point]]''), used to denote [[excitement]], [[surprise]] or [[shock]]: ''Run for your lives'''!''' ''
# In some [[computer language|computer languages]], it is [[colloquially]] called a [[shriek]].
# In some computer languages, it represents a [[Boolean]] ''not'' ("If !''x''" means "if it is not the case that ''x''"). 
# When used in [[e-mail]] to represent a separator for an [[e-mail address]], it is called a [[bang]].
# In mathematics, it is the symbol for [[factorial]].  For example, "5!" is read "five factorial".

